Pairwise intersection refers to selecting one feature from the first input and intersecting it with the features in the second input that it overlaps.</description> </tool> <tool name="Union" type="function" toolboxalias="analysis" attr="mCPU" gallery_group="Overlay Features"> <displayname>Union</displayname> <description>Computes a geometric union of the input features.
